\title{Concept Note: Forecasting Democratic Backsliding with Event Data}
\author{
Serkant, Spencer, Mateo, Scott, Erik \\
}

\date{\today}


\begin{document}

%%%%
\setcounter{page}{1}
\onehalfspacing

Classes of actors:
\begin{itemize}
\item Chief executives
\item Supreme courts
\item Local courts
\item Electoral commissions
\item Police
\item Military
\item Major journalists
\item Media Institutions
\item NGOs
\end{itemize}


Classes of actions:
\begin{itemize}
\item Violence/force:
\begin{itemize}
\item Police violence against peaceful protestors
\item Police violence against members of opposition parties/civil society during demonstrations
\item Arrest/violence against journalists
\item Declare martial law
\item Violent outbreaks during elections
\end{itemize}

\item Freedom of association \& free speech:
\begin{itemize}
\item Using defamation cases to silence any critics
\item Restrictive internet laws
\item Shutting down social media/internet/websites
\item Laws that restrict the right to assembly
\item Incarceration of opposition members
\item Changes to media ownership laws that limit competition or allow for consolidation
\item Limit size of groups that can gather in public/tighten regulations on public demonstrations
\end{itemize}

\item Institutions (EW: I don't understand how some of these are ``institutions''):
\begin{itemize}
\item Imposing broadcast bans on media institutions about issues government do not like them being spread
\item Packing local courts
\item Packing higher courts such as Supreme Court, State Council, and High Council of Judges and Prosecutors
\item Packing the military or the police forces
\item Non-punishment of the executive's corrupt practices (EW: ?)
\item New laws regulating civil service
\item New laws giving the executive nomination powers
\item Erosion of the autonomy/authority of the electoral commission or electoral authorities.
\item Purging members of the ruling party
\item Extending or eliminating terms limits of chief executive
\item Calling irregular elections or constitutional referenda
\item Canceling regularly-scheduled elections
\item Appointment of the President's family members in governmental institutions
\item Changing rules for political competition (i.e. requirements for parties)
\end{itemize}

\item Distraction:
\begin{itemize}
\item{Declarations of strident nationalism, anti-foreign, anti-U.S., etc.}
\item{Sudden emphasis on national security/sovereignty concerns}
\item{Demonization of national/ethnic/religious miniorities}
\item{Demonization of the opposition}
\item{Anti-``elite'' language}
\end{itemize}

EW: these below seem too vague to be actionable
\item Others:
\begin{itemize}
\item Polarization of civil society
\item Increase in demands to international organizations
\item Not allowing International organizations to monitor elections
\item Increased number of corruption cases in the media
\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

